merce id="dd5bab7faeda4613bb5a70782ac99fe1" data-type="product-list"></p><p> If you&#39;re OK with a smaller APS-C sensor, check out the <a data-i13n="cpos:25;pos:1;elm:affiliate_link;sellerN:Adorama;elmt:;" href="https://shopping.yahoo.com/rdlw?merchantId=0eee6f60-6f21-4ba6-b70e-cc15b39bf860&amp;siteId=us-engadget&amp;pageId=1p-autolink&amp;featureId=text-link&amp;merchantName=Adorama&amp;custData=eyJzb3VyY2VOYW1lIjoiV2ViLURlc2t0b3AtVmVyaXpvbiIsInN0b3JlSWQiOiIwZWVlNmY2MC02ZjIxLTRiYTYtYjcwZS1jYzE1YjM5YmY4NjAiLCJsYW5kaW5nVXJsIjoiaHR0cHM6Ly93d3cuYWRvcmFtYS5jb20vaWZqeGgyc2FrLmh0bWw_IiwiY29udGVudFV1aWQiOiI1MzRmOWVlYy0xZmY3LTRmNjUtOGU4Mi1lNTk1Njc3OTQyNjYifQ&amp;signature=AQAAASRSWL0CShUx8vKTjCsWYBlD4wETm67OC77qXIb12oXk&amp;gcReferrer=https%3A%2F%2Fwww.adorama.com%2Fifjxh2sak.html%3F">Fujifilm X-H2S</a> . It has an incredibly fast stacked, backside-illuminated 26.1-megapixel sensor that allows for rapid burst shooting speeds of 40 fps, along with 4K 120p video with minimal rolling shutter. It can capture ProRes 10-bit video internally, has 7 stops of in-body stabilization and a class-leading EVF. Yes, it&#39;s expensive for an APS-C camera at $2,500, but on the other hand, it&#39;s the cheapest stacked sensor camera out there. The other downside is AF that&#39;s not quite up to Canon and Sony&#39;s level.</p><p><core-commerce id="b2d3e1fd30464d13b861fe1ca7f39046" data-type="product-list"></p><p> Video shooters should look at Panasonic&#39;s full-frame <a data-i13n="cpos:26;pos:1;elm:affiliate_link;sellerN:B&amp;H Photo;elmt:;" href="https://shopping.yahoo.com/rdlw?merchantId=95276f3c-7b79-4c1e-803f-981cd9f7a968&amp;siteId=us-engadget&amp;pageId=1p-autolink&amp;featureId=text-link&amp;merchantName=B%26H+Photo&amp;&amp;signature=AQAAAQybzTYum7QVfGHDg5Gn4WF1za5O8Q5fLg1eLfCB2s8d&amp;gcReferrer=https%3A%2F%2Fwww.bhphotovideo.com%2Fc%2Fproduct%2F1742428-REG%2Fpanasonic_dc_s5m2body_lumix_s5_ii_mirrorless.html">S5 II</a> . It&#39;s the company&#39;s first camera with hybrid phase-detect AF designed to make focus &quot;wobble&quot; and other issues a thing of the past. You can shoot sharp 4K 30p video downsampled from the full sensor width, or 4K 60p from an APS-C cropped size, all in 10-bit color. It even offers 5.9K 30p capture, along with RAW 5.9K external output to an Atomos recorder. You also get a flip-out screen for vlogging and updated five-axis in-body stabilization that&#39;s the best in the industry. Photo quality is also good thanks to the dual-gain 24-megapixel sensor. The main drawback is the slowish burst speeds.</p><p><core-commerce id="8518fb9f173a46fe8e787e3f46ff0f9f" data-type="product-list"></p><p> The best value in a new camera is the <a data-i13n="cpos:27;pos:1;elm:affiliate_link;sellerN:Amazon;elmt:;" href="https://shopping.yahoo.com/rdlw?merchantId=66ea567a-c987-4c2e-a2ff-02904efde6ea&amp;siteId=us-engadget&amp;pageId=1p-autolink&amp;featureId=text-link&amp;merchantName=Amazon&amp;&amp;signature=AQAAAcKmUlKAcpPbvoCRub0jL0gKKMefEc2VOJQZ6TG5eept&amp;gcReferrer=https%3A%2F%2Fwww.amazon.com%2FFujifilm-X-T5-Mirrorless-Digital-Camera%2Fdp%2FB0BK2MW5HV">Fujifilm X-T5</a> . It offers a 40-megapixel APS-C sensor, 6.2K video at 30p/4K 60p 10-bit video, 7-stop image stabilization, and shooting speeds up to 20 fps. It&#39;s full of mechanical dials and buttons with Fujifilm&#39;s traditional layout. The downsides are a tilt-only display and autofocus system that can&#39;t keep up with Sony and Canon systems. If you want to go a step up with better video specs for a bit more money, <a data-i13n="cpos:28;pos:1" href="https://shopping.yahoo.com/rdlw?merchantId=95276f3c-7b79-4c1e-803f-981cd9f7a968&amp;siteId=us-engadget&amp;pageId=1p-autolink&amp;featureId=text-link&amp;merchantName=B%26H+Photo&amp;&amp;signature=AQAAAdbGVDSdTYK8nxAyBhHKFqWMyY1XMK0V3xYj4NrqG0i-&amp;gcReferrer=https%3A%2F%2Fwww.bhphotovideo.com%2Fc%2Fproduct%2F1726019-REG%2Ffujifilm_16757045_x_h2_digital_camera_body.html&amp;uuid=dj8sdM5vgrBQUkDG78206">Fuji&#39;s X-H2</a> has the same sensor as the X-T5 but offers 8K 30p video and a flip out display.</p><p> Honorable mentions in this category go to the $2,000 <a data-i13n="cpos:29;pos:1;elm:affiliate_link;sellerN:B&amp;H Photo;elmt:;" href="https://shopping.yahoo.com/rdlw?merchantId=95276f3c-7b79-4c1e-803f-981cd9f7a968&amp;siteId=us-engadget&amp;pageId=1p-autolink&amp;featureId=text-link&amp;merchantName=B%26H+Photo&amp;&amp;signature=AQAAASeN7k6dyb3zfiFzuNJTzl2NWPeGtqAQYKMPcCM3qHBE&amp;gcReferrer=https%3A%2F%2Fwww.bhphotovideo.com%2Fc%2Fproduct%2F1597167-REG%2Fnikon_z_6_ii_mirrorless.html">Nikon Z6 II</a> , which offers excellent image quality, solid video specs and great handling. For budget options, take a look at Sony&#39;s compact full-frame A7C, along with Fujifilm&#39;s older, but still great X-T4.</p><h2> Best mirrorless cameras over $2,500</h2><p><core-commerce id="58ae0163c50842298fda0ebcf515dd4f" data-type="product-list"></p><p> Finally, here are the best cameras if the sky&#39;s the limit in terms of pricing. At the apex is Sony&#39;s 50-megapixel stacked sensor <a data-i13n="cpos:30;pos:1;elm:affiliate_link;sellerN:Amazon;elmt:;" href="https://shopping.yahoo.com/rdlw?merchantId=66ea567a-c987-4c2e-a2ff-02904efde6ea&amp;siteId=us-engadget&amp;pageId=1p-autolink&amp;featureId=text-link&amp;merchantName=Amazon&amp;custData=eyJzb3VyY2VOYW1lIjoiV2ViLURlc2t0b3AtVmVyaXpvbiIsInN0b3JlSWQiOiI2NmVhNTY3YS1jOTg3LTRjMmUtYTJmZi0wMjkwNGVmZGU2ZWEiLCJsYW5kaW5nVXJsIjoiaHR0cHM6Ly93d3cuYW1hem9uLmNvbS9kcC9CMDhWMjI2VDhRP3RhZz1nZGd0MGMtcC1vLWloLTIwIiwiY29udGVudFV1aWQiOiI1MzRmOWVlYy0xZmY3LTRmNjUtOGU4Mi1lNTk1Njc3OTQyNjYifQ&amp;signature=AQAAAWlcJCI8yFo5lc45Hr5yEXqGQ0MTANy2Nz-M_G0AfqLg&amp;gcReferrer=https%3A%2F%2Fwww.amazon.com%2Fdp%2FB08V226T8Q">A1</a> , a stunning high-end camera with a stunning $6,500 price. It rules in performance, with 30 fps shooting speeds and equally quick autofocus that rarely misses a shot. It backs that up with 8K and 4K 120p video shooting, built-in stabilization and the fastest, highest-resolution EVF on the market. The only real drawbacks are the lack of a flip-out screen and, of course, that price.</p><p><core-commerce id="3e5463820381499a8ead4e398d0524cb" data-type="product-list"></p><p> For a bit less money, the <a data-i13n="cpos:31;pos:1;elm:affiliate_link;sellerN:Adorama;elmt:;" href="https://shopping.yahoo.com/rdlw?merchantId=0eee6f60-6f21-4ba6-b70e-cc15b39bf860&amp;siteId=us-engadget&amp;pageId=1p-autolink&amp;featureId=text-link&amp;merchantName=Adorama&amp;custData=eyJzb3VyY2VOYW1lIjoiV2ViLURlc2t0b3AtVmVyaXpvbiIsInN0b3JlSWQiOiIwZWVlNmY2MC02ZjIxLTRiYTYtYjcwZS1jYzE1YjM5YmY4NjAiLCJsYW5kaW5nVXJsIjoiaHR0cHM6Ly93d3cuYWRvcmFtYS5jb20vbmt6OS5odG1sPyIsImNvbnRlbnRVdWlkIjoiNTM0ZjllZWMtMWZmNy00ZjY1LThlODItZTU5NTY3Nzk0MjY2In0&amp;signature=AQAAASKkM6P1x82TSwhuZMepa8nZ3dAkZe8RvPOVzDoJjZFQ&amp;gcReferrer=https%3A%2F%2Fwww.adorama.com%2Fnkz9.html%3F">Nikon Z9</a> packs a 45.7-megapixel stacked sensor that&#39;s so fast, it doesn&#39;t even have a mechanical shutter. It has Nikon&#39;s best autofocus system by far, and delivers outstanding image quality. Video is top notch as well, with 8K 30p internally and 8K 60p RAW via the HDMI port. The main drawbacks are the lack of an articulating display and high price, but it&#39;s a great option if you need speed, resolution and high-end video capabilities.</p><p><core-commerce id="45c2de9c5a314eb6910fe56e2976d1e3" data-type="product-list"></p><p> Tied for the next positions are <a data-i13n="cpos:32;pos:1;elm:affiliate_link;sellerN:Adorama;elmt:;" href="https://shopping.yahoo.com/rdlw?merchantId=0eee6f60-6f21-4ba6-b70e-cc15b39bf860&amp;siteId=us-engadget&amp;pageId=1p-autolink&amp;featureId=text-link&amp;merchantName=Adorama&amp;custData=eyJzb3VyY2VOYW1lIjoiV2ViLURlc2t0b3AtVmVyaXpvbiIsInN0b3JlSWQiOiIwZWVlNmY2MC02ZjIxLTRiYTYtYjcwZS1jYzE1YjM5YmY4NjAiLCJsYW5kaW5nVXJsIjoiaHR0cHM6Ly93d3cuYWRvcmFtYS5jb20vaXNvYTdzbTMuaHRtbD8iLCJjb250ZW50VXVpZCI6IjUzNGY5ZWVjLTFmZjctNGY2NS04ZTgyLWU1OTU2Nzc5NDI2NiJ9&amp;signature=AQAAAQgMZlhE6C11DtROCU1oF2VobB6tUWo2YNj_S653hnK8&amp;gcReferrer=https%3A%2F%2Fwww.adorama.com%2Fisoa7sm3.html%3F">Sony&#39;s A7S III</a> and A7R <a data-i13n="cpos:33;pos:1;elm:affiliate_link;sellerN:B&amp;H Photo;elmt:;" href="https://shopping.yahoo.com/rdlw?merchantId=95276f3c-7b79-4c1e-803f-981cd9f7a968&amp;siteId=us-engadget&amp;pageId=1p-autolink&amp;featureId=text-link&amp;merchantName=B%26H+Photo&amp;&amp;signature=AQAAAZPKeROpQUjolEVvpa6qHMTuPiMxH5ctTI0qxmohIY7Z&amp;gcReferrer=https%3A%2F%2Fwww.bhphotovideo.com%2Fc%2Fproduct%2F1731389-REG%2Fsony_alpha_camera.html">V</a> . With a 61-megapixel sensor, the A7R V shoots sharp and beautiful images at a very respectable speed for such a high-resolution model (10 fps). It has equally fast and reliable autofocus, the sharpest viewfinder on the market and in-body stabilization that&#39;s much improved over the A7R IV. Video has even improved, with 8K and 10-bit options now on tap, albeit with significant rolling shutter. If you don&#39;t need the video, however, Sony&#39;s A7R IVa does mostly the same job, photo-wise, and costs a few hundred dollars less.</p><p> The 12-megapixel A7S III, meanwhile, is the best dedicated video camera, with outstanding 4K video quality at up to 120 fps, a flip-out display and category leading autofocus. It also offers 5-axis in-body stabilization, a relatively compact size and great handling. While the 12-megapixel sensor doesn&#39;t deliver a lot of photo detail, it&#39;s the best camera for low-light shooting, period.</p><p><core-commerce id="38f99f7f7e8a4a35ad3e8e1a6ba92cc1" data-type="product-list"></p><p> And if you want a mirrorless sports camera, check out Canon&#39;s 24-megapixel <a data-i13n="cpos:34;pos:1;elm:affiliate_link;sellerN:Amazon;elmt:;" href="https://shopping.yahoo.com/rdlw?merchantId=66ea567a-c987-4c2e-a2ff-02904efde6ea&amp;siteId=us-engadget&amp;pageId=1p-autolink&amp;featureId=text-link&amp;merchantName=Amazon&amp;&amp;signature=AQAAAYRO-icDxj0aE4Fr6n9_j4p8aprtfOxeosrdxPA6mbjd&amp;gcReferrer=https%3A%2F%2Fwww.amazon.com%2FCanon-4895C002-EOS-R3-Body%2Fdp%2FB09FFTM3F6">EOS R3</a> . It can shoot bursts at up to 30 fps with autofocus enabled, making it great for any fast-moving action. It&#39;s a very solid option for video too, offering 6K at up to 60 fps in Canon&#39;s RAW LTE mode, or 4K at 120 fps. Canon&#39;s Dual Pixel autofocus is excellent, and it offers 8 stops of shake reduction, a flip-out display and even eye detection autofocus. The biggest drawback for the average buyer is the $6,000 price, so it&#39;s really aimed at professionals as a replacement for the 1DX Mark III DSLR.</p><p><core-commerce id="bccf559d59a746d393d328d2fa7011a8" data-type="product-list"></p><p> Honorable mention goes to Canon&#39;s 45 megapixel <a data-i13n="cpos:35;pos:1;elm:affiliate_link;sellerN:B&amp;H Photo;elmt:;" href="https://shopping.yahoo.com/rdlw?merchantId=95276f3c-7b79-4c1e-803f-981cd9f7a968&amp;siteId=us-engadget&amp;pageId=1p-autolink&amp;featureId=text-link&amp;merchantName=B%26H+Photo&amp;&amp;signature=AQAAASPoWgA1cF5rBcYWoXVDQepesVuuOfUdjKNmH_MD_ezC&amp;gcReferrer=https%3A%2F%2Fwww.bhphotovideo.com%2Fc%2Fproduct%2F1547009-REG%2Fcanon_eos_r5_mirrorless_digital.html">EOS R5</a> . For a lot less money, it nearly keeps pace with the A1, thanks to the 20 fps shooting speeds and lightning fast autofocus. It also offers 8K and 4K 120p video, while besting Sony with internal RAW recording. The big drawback is overheating, as you can&#39;t shoot 8K longer than 20 minutes and it takes a while before it cools down enough so that you can start shooting again. Another solid option is <a data-i13n="cpos:36;pos:1;elm:affiliate_link;sellerN:B&amp;H Photo;elmt:;" href="https://shopping.yahoo.com/rdlw?merchantId=95276f3c-7b79-4c1e-803f-981cd9f7a968&amp;siteId=us-engadget&amp;pageId=1p-autolink&amp;featureId=text-link&amp;merchantName=B%26H+Photo&amp;&amp;signature=AQAAAYRSzXsAwyohF2HrzVIUKpFMPBt6RTA1xYPKhZIks_LY&amp;gcReferrer=https%3A%2F%2Fwww.bhphotovideo.com%2Fc%2Fproduct%2F1501344-REG%2Fpanasonic_dc_s1hbody_lumix_dc_s1h_mirrorless_digital.html">Panasonic&#39;s S1H</a> , a Netflix-approved mirrorless camera that can handle 6K video and RAW shooting.</p><p> You&#39;re now caught up, new models have been arriving thick and fast, including potential rumored <a data-i13n="cpos:37;pos:1" href="https://www.canonrumors.com/canon-teases-canon-eos-r8-and-canon-eos-r50-announcement-happening-this-week/">APS-C models from Canon</a> . Another known model coming in May is <a data-i13n="cpos:38;pos:1" href="https://www.engadget.com/clean-hydrogen-fuel-split-seawater-214042411.html">Panasonic&#39;s S5 IIx</a> , which offers the same features of the S5 II plus internal SSD recording and live streaming for just $200 more. We&#39;ll have full coverage of those when they arrive, so stay glued to Engadget.com for the latest updates.</p><p></p> This article originally appeared on Engadget at https://www.engadget.com/best-mirrorless-cameras-133026494.html?src=rss]]>; </description><link/><![CDATA[https://www.engadget.com/best-mirrorless-cameras-133026494.html?src=rss]]><source_id> engadget_479</source_id><guid ispermalink="false"> 534f9eec-1ff7-4f65-8e82-e59567794266</guid><dc:creator>史蒂夫·登特</dc:creator><source/><![CDATA[Engadget]]><dc:publisher>恩杰特</dc:publisher><dc:rightsholder>恩杰特</dc:rightsholder><pubDate>Thu, 03 Aug 2023 14:00:05 +0000</pubDate><ingested> 1691071206</ingested><modified> 2023-08-03T14:00:19+00:00 </modified><category><![CDATA[Consumer Discretionary]]></category><category><![CDATA[Cameras & Photography]]></category><category><![CDATA[Shopping]]></category><category><![CDATA[Technology & Electronics]]></category><category><![CDATA[site|engadget]]></category><category><![CDATA[provider_name|Engadget]]></category><category><![CDATA[region|US]]></category><category><![CDATA[language|en-US]]></category><category><![CDATA[author_name|Steve Dent]]></category><media:content height="1012" medium="image" url="https://s.yimg.com/os/creatr-uploaded-images/2023-03/a269d900-be8f-11ed-acce-00e9e8001fc4" width="1800"><media:keywords>标题</media:keywords><media:media_html><![CDATA[ ]]></media:media_html><dc:identifier><![CDATA[1]]></dc:identifier><media:credit><![CDATA[ ]]></media:credit><media:description><![CDATA[ ]]></media:description><media:title><![CDATA[ ]]></media:title></media:content><media:content height="1012" medium="image" url="https://media-mbst-pub-ue1.s3.amazonaws.com/creatr-uploaded-images/2023-03/a269d900-be8f-11ed-acce-00e9e8001fc4" width="1800"><media:media_html><![CDATA[ ]]></media:media_html><dc:identifier><![CDATA[2]]></dc:identifier><media:credit><![CDATA[Steve Dent / Engadget]]></media:credit><media:description><![CDATA[The Sony A7S camera sits on a round white patio table outdoors, with its view screen flipped around to point the display forward. In the background is a group of trees at the edge of a backyard at dawn or dusk showing a dramatic sun cutting through the leaves.]]></media:description><media:title><![CDATA[Sony A7S]]></media:title></media:content></item><item><title><![CDATA[Waymo is bringing its driverless ride-hailing service to Austin]]></title><description type="html"><![CDATA[<p> Waymo 今年早些时候才<a data-i13n="cpos:1;pos:1" href="https://www.engadget.com/waymo-is-starting-driverless-taxi-tests-in-los-angeles-200542496.html">刚刚抵达洛杉矶</a>，但这并没有阻止其进一步扩张。该公司正在将其 Waymo One 乘车服务<a data-i13n="cpos:2;pos:1" href="https://waymo.com/blog/2023/08/waymo-one-heads-to-austin.html">扩展</a>到奥斯汀。第一阶段将于今年秋天开始，未来几个月将推出完全无人驾驶的运营和公共乘车服务。 Waymo 声称，该覆盖范围将“真正有用”——它应该覆盖德克萨斯州首府的主要地区，包括市中心以及巴顿山和海德公园等著名地区。您今天可以加入<a data-i13n="cpos:3;pos:1" href="https://waymo.com/waitlist/">候补名单</a>。</p><p>这次部署可以说是一次回归，因为 Waymo 选择奥斯汀在其家乡山景城之外进行<a data-i13n="cpos:4;pos:1" href="https://www.engadget.com/2015-07-07-google-self-driving-tests-austin-texas.html">一些首次自动驾驶测试</a>。该公司还于 2015 年在公共街道上推出了首款完全自动驾驶汽车，创造了历史。自春季以来，这个 Alphabet 旗下品牌一直在该市<a data-i13n="cpos:5;pos:1" href="https://www.engadget.com/waymo-brings-its-fleet-of-new-self-driving-suvs-to-austin-165720284.html">测试其自动驾驶 SUV</a> 。</p><span id="end-legacy-contents"></span><p>奥斯汀将成为继凤凰城、旧金山和洛杉矶之后第四个获得 Waymo One 的城市。 The firm also briefly mapped <a data-i13n="cpos:6;pos:1" href="https://www.engadget.com/waymo-self-driving-cars-new-york-city-130044539.html">New York City</a> , although it hasn&#39;t announced plans to offer commercial service in the region.虽然通常只在这些城市的有限区域提供乘车服务，但 Waymo 最近将其运营区域扩大了一倍，涵盖了凤凰城地区和旧金山的更大范围。</p><p>该公告反映出 Waymo 对网约车业务的更加重视。该公司最近<a data-i13n="cpos:7;pos:1" href="https://www.engadget.com/waymo-pushes-back-its-self-driving-truck-efforts-to-focus-on-ride-hailing-211355559.html">推迟了其自动卡车运输计划</a>，以帮助其专注于客运服务。 Waymo 希望 One 首先成为商业热门，这意味着扩大业务并获得吸引付费客户的许可。当<a data-i13n="cpos:8;pos:1" href="https://www.engadget.com/cruises-robotaxis-are-heading-to-houston-and-dallas-094531398.html">Cruise</a>和<a data-i13n="cpos:9;pos:1" href="https://www.engadget.com/toyota-aurora-robotaxi-texas-test-181751763.html">Aurora</a>等竞争对手在德克萨斯州进行测试时，我们面临着迅速采取行动的压力。</p><p>总体增长存在一些障碍。例如，出于安全考虑，官员们希望<a data-i13n="cpos:10;pos:1" href="https://www.engadget.com/san-francisco-asks-california-regulators-to-halt-or-slow-driverless-vehicle-testing-083906662.html">停止或减缓旧金山机器人出租车的部署</a>。 Waymo 和通用汽车 Cruise 的车辆<a data-i13n="cpos:11;pos:1" href="https://www.engadget.com/cruise-driverless-taxis-blocked-san-francisco-traffic-for-hours-robotaxi-gm-204000451.html">堵塞了交通</a>，干扰了急救人员并造成了其他问题。其他城市和州也没有为自动驾驶汽车开绿灯。不过，德克萨斯州对技术的开放态度可能会有所帮助，而且 Waymo 指出，奥斯汀快速增长的经济（美国主要城市中第二快的经济）可能会帮助其获得机会。</p>本文最初发表在 Engadget 上：https://www.engadget.com/waymo-is-bringing-its-driverless-ride-hailing-service-to-austin-133949180.html?src=rss]]>; </description><link/><![CDATA[https://www.engadget.com/waymo-is-bringing-its-driverless-ride-hailing-service-to-austin-133949180.html?src=rss]]><source_id> engadget_479</source_id><guid ispermalink="false"> 1b8c76df-6e12-4cba-985c-920c0c2a9b70</guid><dc:creator>乔恩·芬加斯</dc:creator><source/><![CDATA[